This paper discusses the use of deep learning models in classification tasks and the need to quantify the reliability of a model's prediction on individual samples, especially in safety-critical domains. This suggests that the paper belongs to the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Computer Vision (cs.CV), Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE), and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) as these are the most relevant areas for the topic of the paper.
